Release Note:
-------------

This is version 0.9 of the BangDB Server.

The tar file (bangdb-server-[32/64]bits-[build]-[version].tar.gz) contains following;

a. bangdb-server (the server exe)
b. libbangdb-client.so.0.9
c. README
d. bangdb.config
e. install.sh
f. uninstall.sh
g. include - dir for headers
h. bangdb_bench - dir that contains sample test file for server

uncompress the file by running;
tar -xzf bangdb-server-64bits-XX-XX.tar.gz

cd to the dir (bangdb-server) and run the server

cd bangdb-server
./bangdb-server

open a new terminal and install the client library
cd client-linux
bash install.sh

To test the server with the supplied test/bench files, go the bangdb_bench dir and
compile the bench using the supplied build.sh file or otherwise

cd bangdb_bench
bash build.sh

to run the test file us
./bench

etc...

Please see more information on progarmming with server at http://iqlect.com/manual_bangdb_server_development.php
